:::summary
Linux is a free, open-source Unix-like operating system kernel first released by Linus Torvalds in 1991. Combined with the GNU userland tools, it forms a complete operating system used on the vast majority of the world's servers, supercomputers, Android smartphones, embedded systems, and cloud infrastructure. Linux is the crowning achievement of the open-source software movement — built collaboratively by thousands of contributors worldwide.
